5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to solar power; to prohibit the construction
10 and operation of new solar power facilities and carbon dioxide
11 storage facilities for one year, subject to conditions.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. (a) For purposes of this section, the
14 following terms have the following meanings:
15 (1)SOLAR POWER FACILITY. A large-scale, ground-mounted
16 installation of photovoltaic panels that are designed to
17 generate electricity using solar power for use off-site or
18 sale to a third party, including all equipment and facilities
19 required to operate the facility and transmit generated
20 electricity.
21 (2) UNDER CONSTRUCTION. Construction of a solar power
22 facility has begun pursuant to Internal Revenue Service
23 regulations adopted pursuant to 26 U.S.C. §§ 45Y and 48E
24 defining beginning of construction and any other regulations,
25 procedures, or other published information or guidance
26 pursuant to that federal law.
27 (b) For one year after the effective date of this act,
28 a solar power facility not operating or under construction on
Page 1

a solar power facility not operating or under construction on
SB354 Engrossed
29 the effective date of this act may not be constructed or
30 operated unless a proposed solar power facility operator holds
31 a public hearing, after 30 days notice, on the proposed solar
32 power facility in the county in which the proposed solar power
33 facility will be located.
34 (c) This act shall only apply to counties contiguous to
35 the Gulf of America due to the significant population
36 increases therein, limited availability of suitable real
37 property, and need to protect the unique environmental aspects
38 of river deltas and the gulf.
39 (d) For one year after the effective date of this act,
40 the governing body of a county, municipality, or other
41 political subdivision of this state may not adopt an
42 ordinance, regulation, or other policy related to a proposed
43 or existing solar power facility that is more stringent than
44 the requirements of this section.
45 Section 2. (a) For purposes of this section, the term
46 "carbon dioxide storage facility" shall mean a storage
47 facility used for the storage and sequestration of carbon
48 dioxide, as contemplated in Article 6, Chapter 17, Title 9,
49 Code of Alabama 1975, which is located on public land or which
50 is 50,000 acres or more in size.
51 (b) For one year after the effective date of this act,
52 a carbon dioxide storage facility not operating or under
53 construction on the effective date of this act may not be
54 constructed or operated.
55 Section 3. This act shall become effective immediately.
